[Student "S"]
{Partner's 2\H is a positive response, 8+ points with a 5+ card suit.  

Even though it is tempting, bidding RKCB now would be a mistake because of your doubleton \S loser. Instead just support the \Hs. Partner cannot pass, you both know you are forced to game. In fact, partner bids 3\S.  

Partner promises first round \S control so NOW you can bid RCKB. When you bid 4NT partner answers 6\H. This shows 1 Key-Card and a void in a suit higher than \Hs. Knowing you are missing either the \DA or \HK you pass.}

